Tweet_Content: KenPom has been like the basketball bible for me but Its getting to the point I cant take it seriously. Kentucky No. 33 Auburn 35 while seven-loss BYU No. 20 seven-loss Ohio St at 13 ten-loss Purdue No. 24 among others.
Comment_Content: Kenpom does not factor in whether a team wins or loses...only score matters...1 point win is essentially the same in the kenpom as a 1 point lost.  (Only fractions of a difference).

Tweet_Content: KenPom has been like the basketball bible for me but Its getting to the point I cant take it seriously. Kentucky No. 33 Auburn 35 while seven-loss BYU No. 20 seven-loss Ohio St at 13 ten-loss Purdue No. 24 among others.
Comment_Content: KenPom like all other computer rankings is margin of victory driven (adjusted for sos). If UK were to beat the top 10 kenpom teams by 1 pt each they would be ranked lower than a team that lost to kenpom teams ranked 41-45 by 1 pt each but beat teams 46 thru 50 by 30 points each.

Tweet_Content: KenPom has been like the basketball bible for me but Its getting to the point I cant take it seriously. Kentucky No. 33 Auburn 35 while seven-loss BYU No. 20 seven-loss Ohio St at 13 ten-loss Purdue No. 24 among others.
